<C>__{miss krause}
<D>__{they say that no one dies here. they say your factory is a haven. they say you are good.}
<A>__{schindler's face changes like a wall going up, a mask of indifference like in the portrait of adolf hitler on the wall behind him.}
<C>__{schindler}
<D>__{who says that?}
<C>__{miss krause}
<D>__{everyone.}
<A>__{schindler glances away from her. he seems weary suddenly, depressed.}
<C>__{miss krause}
<D>__{my name is regina perlman, not elsa krause. i've been living in cracow on false papers since the ghetto massacre.}
<P>__{(pause)}
<D>__{my parents are in plaszow. they're old. they're killing old people in plaszow now. they bury them up in the forest. i have no money. i borrowed these clothes. will you bring them here?}
<A>__{schindler glances back at her, his face hard, cold, and studies her for a long, long moment before }
<C>__{schindler}
<D>__{i don't do that. you've been misled. i ask one thing: whether or not a worker has certain skills. that's what i ask and that's what i care about, get out of my office.}
